                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#134v" facs="137">Fol. 134v</locus>
                    Greeting to Michael. Not in Chaîne 1913. Written in a different hand.
                    Incipit: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሰላም፡ ለከ፡ መላአከ (sic)፡  ኪዳኑ፡ (ወ)ምክሩ፡</foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <desc>
                    Designs have been painted on the top edge, bottom edge, and fore edge of the folios that are visible when the codex is closed
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#ir(ecto) #134r #135r #135v" facs="001 136 137 138">Fols. ir(ecto), 134r, 135r, 135v</locus>
                    blank
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#iir(ecto)" facs="002">Fol. iir(ecto)</locus>
                    geometric designs and pen trials
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e4">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#iiv(erso)" facs="003">Fol. iiv(erso)</locus>
                    illegible pen trials
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e5">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#51r" facs="053">Fol. 51r</locus>
                    The midpoint of the Psalms is marked with three strophes written in alternating red and black characters
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a2">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#133r" facs="135">Fol. 133r</locus>
                    concluding prayers mention the owner Wäldä Giyo[r]gis (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ወልደ፡ ጊዮ[ር]ጊስ፡</foreign>), the scribe Wäldä ʾAmanuʾel (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ወልደ፡ አማኑኤል፡</foreign>), and emperor Mǝnilǝk II (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ምኒልክ፡</foreign>), who reigned from 1889–1913
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e6">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#1 #12 #27 #38 #55 #67 #89 #102 #120" facs="003 014 029 040 057 069 091 104 122">Fols. 1, 12, 27, 38, 55, 67, 89, 102, 120</locus>
                    red string stitched into fore edge as navigation system
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e7">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#6 #62 #97" facs="008 064 099">Fols. 6, 62, 97</locus>
                    yellow string stitched into fore edge as navigation system
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e8">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#19 #92" facs="021 094">Fols. 19, 92</locus>
                    blue string stitched into fore edge as navigation system
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e9">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#33" facs="035">Fol. 33</locus>
                    yellow and black string stitched into fore edge as navigation system
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e10">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#46" facs="048">Fol. 46</locus>
                    multi-colored string stitched into fore edge as navigation system
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e11">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#78" facs="080">Fol. 78</locus>
                    brown string stitched into fore edge as navigation system
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e12">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#113" facs="115">Fol. 113</locus>
                    black string stitched into fore edge as navigation system
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e13">
                    <desc>
                    Numbered quires: quires 2–14
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e14">
                    <desc>
                      words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#30r #38v #42r #54v #99v" facs="032 041 044 057 102">folss. 30r, 38v, 42r, 54v, 99v, </locus>, etc.) #occasionally these are located with a symbol (┴) (e.g., <locus target="#54v #108r" facs="057 110">54v, 108r, </locus>);
                      lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#102r #118v" facs="104 121">102r, 118v, </locus>);
                      erasure markings are visible (<locus target="#102r" facs="104">102r, </locus>);
                      text has been removed (<locus target="#57r #130r" facs="059 132">57r, 130r</locus>)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
